cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.CC

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques for recognizing lexical entailment. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves supervised learning techniques, which suggests the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses vector space models of semantics, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also evaluates the approaches using different datasets, which could be relevant to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
